I think this has the right ingredients, but got taken out of the oven too soon. There are inklings of a subtext here that should probably be more textual, and the interview could use a little more work. In particular, I dislike the overuse of ellipses to show grief; in most cases, words carry more emotional weight when punctuated with a single period. Ellipses just make her sound sleepy.







